\par

\pard\f0\fs28  {\b P. munitum} (Kaulfuss) C. Presl, {\i Tent. Pteridogr.} 83 (1836), from W. North America, like {\b 1} but the lamina 6-18 cm wide, lanceolate, and the pinnae narrower, with forward-directed or incurved teeth, is cultivated for ornament and is occasionally naturalized in W. Europe.
