\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. P. setiferum} (Forskål) Woynar, {\i Mitt. Naturw. Ver. Steierm}.{\b  49:} 181 (1913) ({\i P. aculeatum} auct., non (L.) Roth,{\i  P. aculeatum} subsp.{\i  angulare} (Kit. ex Willd.) Vollmann,{\i  D. setifera} (Forskål) Woynar,{\i  P. angulare} (Kit. ex Willd.) C. Presl, {\i Aspidium aculeatum} sensu Swartz). Rhizome thick, woody. Leaves 30-120 cm, soft, usually not persistent; lamina 10-25 cm wide, lanceolate, 2-pinnate; pinnae up to 40 on each side; pinnules serrate, distinctly stalked, not decurrent; proximal acroscopic pinnule scarcely longer than the rest, the proximal side rounded below, the distal obtusely auricled, the 2 sides forming an obtuse angle at the base. Indusium thin. 2n = 82.{\i  S., W. & C. Europe.} Al Au Az Be Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Ge Gr Hb He ?Ho Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs (K) Sa Si Tu.
