\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. P. braunii} (Spenner) Fée, {\i Mém. Fam. Foug.}{\b  5:} 278 (1852) ({\i P. paleaceum} auct., non (Borkh.) O. Schwarz,{\i  Dryopteris braunii }(Spenner) Underw., {\i Aspidium braunii} Spenner). Leaves up to 80 cm, soft, usually dying in autumn; lamina up to 20 cm wide, oblong-lanceolate, generally 2-pinnate; pinnae up to 40 on each side; pinnules up to 15 on each side, softly hairy above, the margins serrate; proximal acroscopic pinnule not larger than the rest; pinnules sessile or subsessile, obliquely decurrent, not or scarcely auricled, acutely angled at the base. 2n = 164.{\i  Woodland and shady places. S. & C. Norway; C. Europe, extending locally to C. Spain and E. Russia}. Au Cz Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, E) Su.
